text: The Boonoo Boonoo National Park (pronounced: 'Banna-Banuh' Boonoo Boonoo National Park. NSW Environment & Heritage Office ) is a national park in the northeast of the Australian state of New South Wales, around 571 km north of Sydney and 26 km northeast of Tenterfield on Mount Lindesay Road. The park has an area of 43.77 km2 and was founded on March 19, 1982. The Boonoo Boonoo River flows through a narrow valley with the rainforest in the park and forms a 210 m tall waterfall. Forest walks, swimming and camping in the forest are among the most popular recreational activities. == References == == Other websites == * Boonoo Boonoo National Park Category:National parks in Australia
title: Boonoo Boonoo National Park
